tion). Egocentric, not willing to further education (professional development). So mixed.\n\nCandidate B: handles stress well (good under pressure). Very conscientious (reliability). Good weather assessment (technical). Excellent computer skills (technical). But grumpy, uncooperative (teamwork negative). No explicit teamwork strengths. So teamwork is a concern.\n\nCandidate A: anticipates dangerous situations (good judgment). Sees complex connections (cognitive). Excellent spatial vision (technical). Very good leadership (teamwork). But unorganized, poor at taking criticism (reliability/communication). No explicit stress handling. Leadership suggests teamwork but not explicit.\n\nCandidate D: responds adequately to unexpected events (good under pressure). Concentrates well, solves problems extremely well (technical). Takes responsibility seriously (reliability). Weak leadership, arrogant (teamwork/communication). No explicit teamwork strengths.\n\nWe need to choose best overall for long-distance flights. Long-distance requires reliability, decision-making, stress handling, teamwork with crew, professional development.\n\nCandidate C seems reliable, good decision-making, positive crew atmosphere, but communication difficulty and lack of willingness to develop may be problematic for long flights where clear communication is vital. Egocentric may affect crew cooperation.\n\nCandidate B handles stress well, conscientious, but uncooperative and grumpy, no teamwork strengths.\n\nCandidate A has strong anticipation and leadership, but unorganized and poor at criticism, unknown stress handling.\n\nCandidate D has strong problem solving and responsibility, but weak leadership and arrogance.\n\nWhich candidate balances? Possibly Candidate A: leadership, anticipation, cognitive abilities, but need to consider unorganized and criticism. For long flights, organization is crucial. That is a serious weakness.\n\nCandidate D: problem solving, responsibility, concentration, but weak leadership and arrogance may affect crew.\n\nCandidate C: reliability, quick decisions, positive atmosphere, but communication difficulty and unwillingness to develop may be serious.\n\nCandidate B: stress handling, conscientious, but uncooperative.\n\nWe need to weigh seriousness. Communication difficulty for C is a direct safety issue. Uncooperative for B also safety. Unorganized for A also safety. Weak leadership for D also safety.\n\nWhich is least severe? Perhaps D's weak leadership but strong problem solving and responsibility; arrogance may affect crew but can be mitigated? However D's leadership is weak, which is important for pilot.\n\nC's communication difficulty is a big issue; also unwillingness to develop.\n\nB's uncooperative is also big.\n\nA's unorganized may affect flight planning.\n\nAll have issues. Need to decide provisional preference. Maybe Candidate A because leadership and anticipation are crucial, and unorganized can be mitigated with support; also no explicit communication weakness (only criticism). So I will provisionally prefer A.\n\nState uncertainty and what would change: if others have positive stress handling for A or teamwork strengths for D, could shift.\n\nProceed."}
